triage.prompt:
You are the orchestrator brain. Below are read-only audit reports from multiple models ({models}) for round {round}. Read CLAUDE.md and GLOBAL_DEV_PROMPT.md. Produce a SINGLE deduplicated, prioritized fix plan as STRICT JSON (no prose, no markdown fences) matching this schema:
{"tasks": [{"slug": "kebab-id", "title": "...", "severity": "critical|high|medium|low", "difficulty": "easy|medium|hard", "files": ["path", ...], "instruction": "precise, self-contained fix instruction citing exact file:line and the target end-state"}]}
Rules: (1) Merge findings multiple models agree on; prefer their consensus. (2) Order by ROI: silent-fallback correctness fires first, then NATIVE-FIRST migrations (plain Python on hot paths -> Rust/C++/Cython/Numba/Triton — these are a funded priority, rank them high), then god-file/god-function splits and dead-code removal, then duplication, then remaining perf, then hygiene. (3) difficulty=hard for risky refactors touching untested core, scoring, native kernels, or any change that could move scoring numbers; difficulty=easy for mechanical deletions/trim/lazy-imports. (4) Each task must be independently committable and gated. (5) NEVER propose reverting a novel mechanism to softmax/attention. (6) Emit at most {max_tasks} tasks this round, highest-ROI first. Output ONLY the JSON object.

--- FINDINGS ---
{findings}

fix.prompt:
Apply EXACTLY this one fix and nothing else. Read CLAUDE.md and GLOBAL_DEV_PROMPT.md first. Before editing, use the code-review-graph MCP (semantic_search_nodes / query_graph) to check callers/dependents/duplicates. Make the minimal correct change, preserve behavior, keep type hints, add no dead code. Do NOT touch files outside the listed set. Do NOT revert any novel mechanism to softmax/attention — if a gate abandons the novel branch, that is the bug to fix, not to follow. When done, briefly state what changed. The change will be gated by smoke tests + a fixed-seed scoring diff; if you cannot make the change safely within the listed files, STOP and explain instead of guessing.

TASK: {title}
SEVERITY: {severity}
FILES: {files}
INSTRUCTION:
{instruction}
